THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. Chapter 202 of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. No person shall intentionally release, organize the release
4 of or intentionally cause to be released 10 or more balloons
5 inflated with a gas that is lighter than air within a 24-hour period.
6 2. A person who violates the provisions of subsection 1 is
7 subject to a civil penalty not to exceed $250. Each balloon released
8 in a 24-hour period in excess of the limit imposed in subsection 1
9 constitutes a separate violation.
10 3. A civil penalty imposed pursuant to subsection 2 must be
11 recovered in a civil action brought by the Attorney General or by
12 the district attorney or city attorney for the jurisdiction in which
13 the violation occurred.
14 4. Any civil penalty collected pursuant to this section by:
15 (a) The Attorney General must be paid to the State Treasurer
16 for credit to the State General Fund.
17 (b) A district attorney or city attorney must be deposited in the
18 county or city treasury, as applicable.
19 5. The Attorney General or the district attorney or city
20 attorney of a county or city, as applicable, in which a person
21 releases a balloon in violation of subsection 1 may bring an action
22 to enjoin the violation.
23 6. As used in this section, “balloon” means any balloon made
24 of nonbiodegradable material or biodegradable material that
25 requires more than 5 minutes of contact with air or water to
26 degrade. The term does not include:
27 (a) A hot air balloon that is recovered after launching;
28 (b) A balloon used in a governmental or scientific research
29 project; or
30 (c) A balloon that is released and remains indoors.
